snippet.textDisplay: Makes me mad that they said he was spun out, I am an avid race fan and was watching it live. The car who was behind him before he spun had a run and was going way faster than Newman and Newman threw a block. Anybody would've done the same thing as both drivers. I'm glad Newman is ok, but it ticks me off when someone says "spun him out" or "wrecked him" because it was in no way intentional, I just wish they would get their facts straight before making it seem like a deliberate act on the other drivers, who were only concerned about Newman and his injuries. I'm glad he's ok and has no life threatening injuries though, Newman is a well respected driver and person. I hope he has a speedy but good recovery.
